# Cursor Rules for Terraform ROSA Project

Please refer to [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) for complete project guidelines, conventions, and best practices.

Key points:
- Files use numeric prefixes: 00-19 (infrastructure), 20 (cluster access), 21-29 (workloads), 90-99 (outputs)
- Use Makefile targets for common operations (see `make help`)
- Shell variables in provisioners use single `$` (Terraform only interpolates `${...}`)
- Private clusters cannot use cluster login or GitOps deployment
- Default to HCP clusters (`TF_VAR_hosted_control_plane=true` by default)
- **Before committing**: Run `make pr` to validate, check formatting, and run linting (or `make test` for full suite including plan)

See AGENTS.md for detailed documentation.
